<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="662" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/441: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-24T18:00:00-05:00">March 24, 1931—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>18. Your 52, March 23, 2 p.m. The Department would view with
                                satisfaction any arrangement acceptable to both Honduras and
                                Nicaragua, but considers inadvisable any attempt to influence the
                                negotiations for the present at least until the views of both
                                parties are more concretely defined so that it would be possible to
                                work towards a solution agreeable to both.</p>
                            <p>Please repeat to Managua.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>